installed tomcat6 on my Ubuntu machine
--------------------------------------
sudo apt-get install tomcat6

deployed the war
----------------
cp tutorial.war /var/lib/tomcat6/webapps/

Access the tutorial app
-----------------------
http://localhost:8080/tutorial/holidayService/holiday.wsdl

http://localhost:8080/tutorial/holidayService/


Create simple Webservice log
----------------------------

started from this excellent tutorial:
http://blog.espenberntsen.net/2010/02/26/generate-jaxb-classes-from-an-xsd-schema-and-the-schema-from-an-xml-sample-document/

how to generate an XSD schema from a sample XML document 

<addRequest>
  <value>1</value>
  <value>2</value>
</addRequest>

The XSD schema is generated from the sample using the Trang project which lives here: http://code.google.com/p/jing-trang/

build -f build-generate-schema.xml

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<xs:schema xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" elementFormDefault="qualified">
  <xs:element name="addRequest">
    <xs:complexType>
      <xs:sequence>
        <xs:element maxOccurs="unbounded" ref="value"/>
      </xs:sequence>
    </xs:complexType>
  </xs:element>
  <xs:element name="value" type="xs:integer"/>
</xs:schema>


Generating class files from XSD using JAXB
------------------------------------------

From Java 1.6 on JAXB is included! So nothing to install/download here. This will generate some class files in the src/org/testingsoftware/org/generated folder:
ant -f build-generate-jaxb.xml


Where is the WSDL?
------------------

You donâ€™t need to create a WSDL file with Spring WS.


Deploy the demo_server webservice and start Tomcat
--------------------------------------------------

Copy the demo_server.0.1.war to your Tomcat webapps folder. Then start Tomcat:
./server.sh

Now you can access the new service:
http://localhost:8080/demo_server.0.1/calc-service/calcServiceDefinition.wsdl

